U.K. Pound Strengthens Against Euro Before Bank of England Rate Decision

-- B y   L u k a n y o   M n y a n d a
-- 
2011-09-08T10:36:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/u-k-pound-strengthens-against-euro-before-bank-of-england-rate-decision.html
The pound strengthened against the
euro before the Bank of England announces its decision on
interest rates and asset purchases.  Sterling advanced 0.3 percent to 87.89 pence per euro as of
 11:35 a.m. in London, after weakening by as much as 0.3 percent
to 88.42 pence. It was little changed at $1.5977.  The Bank of England will announce its interest-rate
decision at noon in London.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lukanyo Mnyanda in Edinburgh at 
 lmnyanda@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tim Farrand at 
 tfarrand@bloomberg.net  